This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on learning distributed sentence representations. Additionally, the use of a convolutional neural network as an encoder and a long short-term memory recurrent neural network as a decoder is a common approach in natural language processing research, which falls under the cs.CL category. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. 

Furthermore, the use of neural networks for prediction tasks could place this paper in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. 

The paper's use of convolutional neural networks could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category, as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image processing and computer vision research. 

Finally, the use of a hierarchical encoder-decoder model could place this paper in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category, as this type of model is commonly used in neural network research.
